The paper discusses cooperative beamforming in wireless sensor networks, which involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the intricacies of varying beamforming gains, which is related to system dynamics and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance improvement offered by the CB gain, which is related to machine learning (cs.MM) and learning theory (cs.LG).
